	"title": "Week 6",
	"content": "<h1 class=\"page-title\">Week 6</h1>\n  \n  <div id=\"todo-date-mount-point\"></div>\n  \n    <p><strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Overview</span></strong></p>\n<div class=\"page\" title=\"Page 1\">\n<div class=\"section\" style=\"background-color: rgb(100.000000%, 100.000000%, 100.000000%);\">\n<div class=\"layoutArea\">\n<div class=\"column\">\n<div class=\"page\" title=\"Page 1\">\n<div class=\"section\" style=\"background-color: rgb(100.000000%, 100.000000%, 100.000000%);\">\n<div class=\"layoutArea\">\n<div class=\"column\">\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: 'NimbusSanL';\">Interest rates and inflation (determining factors, nominal vs real interest rates, Fischer effect), historical returns (return calculation, historical distribution of returns), return statistics (mean return and return volatility, normal distributions vs fat tails, probability distributions), downside risk, returns of long-term investments (long-run vs short-run returns, compounding effects, lognormal distributions)<br></span></p>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: 'NimbusSanL';\">&nbsp;</span></p>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Learning Objectives</span></strong></p>\n<p>Upon completion of this week, you will be able to understand:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>the difference between nominal vs real interest rates</li>\n<li>the determinant factors of interest rates and inflation</li>\n<li>how to calculate returns</li>\n<li>how to build historical distributions of returns and calculate basic statistics from them</li>\n<li>different types of return distributions commonly encountered in financial markets</li>\n<li>extreme events, distributions with fat tails, and downside risk</li>\n<li>distinction between historical vs probability distribution</li>\n<li>short-run vs long-run returns</li>\n</ul>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Preparation for class</span></strong></p>\n<p>Mandatory reading:</p>\n<p>Lecture 3: <span class=\"instructure_file_holder link_holder instructure_file_link_holder\"><a id=\"80589757\" class=\"inline_disabled preview_in_overlay\" title=\"Link\" href=\"https://canvas.colorado.edu/courses/123249/files/80666368?wrap=1\" target=\"_blank\" data-canvas-previewable=\"true\" data-api-endpoint=\"https://canvas.colorado.edu/api/v1/courses/123249/files/80666368\" data-api-returntype=\"File\">lecture 3.pdf</a><a class=\"file_download_btn\" role=\"button\" download=\"\" style=\"margin-inline-start: 5px; text-decoration: none;\" href=\"https://canvas.colorado.edu/courses/123249/files/80666368/download?download_frd=1\"><span role=\"presentation\"><svg viewBox=\"0 0 1920 1920\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" style=\"width:1em; height:1em; vertical-align:middle; fill:currentColor\">\n    <path d=\"m1807.093 1482.477 79.736 79.963-355.313 355.312H355.346L.035 1562.44l79.85-79.963 322.22 322.334H1484.76l322.334-322.334ZM997.677-.033v1167.02l355.313-355.313 79.962 79.85-491.858 491.633L449.46 891.524l79.962-79.85 355.313 355.313V-.033h112.941Z\" fill-rule=\"evenodd\"></path>\n</svg>\n</span><span class=\"screenreader-only\">Download lecture 3.pdf</span></a></span></p>\n<p>Lecture 3 supplement (FRB's Monetary policy in detail): <span class=\"instructure_file_holder link_holder instructure_file_link_holder\"><a class=\"inline_disabled preview_in_overlay\" title=\"lecture 3 sup.pdf\" href=\"https://canvas.colorado.edu/courses/123249/files/80666940?wrap=1\" target=\"_blank\" data-canvas-previewable=\"false\" data-api-endpoint=\"https://canvas.colorado.edu/api/v1/courses/123249/files/80666940\" data-api-returntype=\"File\">lecture 3 sup.pdf</a><a class=\"file_download_btn\" role=\"button\" download=\"\" style=\"margin-inline-start: 5px; text-decoration: none;\" href=\"https://canvas.colorado.edu/courses/123249/files/80666940/download?download_frd=1\"><span role=\"prese